The MIB defines two indices for the upsHighPrecBatteryPackTable, but the device
actually returns three which causes errors in the scrape. The third index always
matches the second in my testing.

--- a/apc/PowerNet-MIB
+++ b/apc/PowerNet-MIB
@@ -15684,7 +15684,7 @@ upsHighPrecBatteryPackTableSize OBJECT-TYPE
        DESCRIPTION
                "An entry containing information applicable to a
                particular battery pack."
-       INDEX { upsHighPrecBatteryPackIndex, upsHighPrecBatteryCartridgeIndex }
+       INDEX { upsHighPrecBatteryPackIndex, upsHighPrecBatteryCartridgeIndex, upsHighPrecBatteryExtraIndex }
        ::= { upsHighPrecBatteryPackTable 1 }

    UPSHighPrecBatteryPackEntry ::= SEQUENCE {
@@ -15700,6 +15700,15 @@ upsHighPrecBatteryPackTableSize OBJECT-TYPE
        upsHighPrecBatteryPackCartridgeStatus       OCTET STRING
    }

+   upsHighPrecBatteryExtraIndex OBJECT-TYPE
+       SYNTAX     INTEGER
+       ACCESS     read-only
+       STATUS     mandatory
+       DESCRIPTION
+               "The original MIB includes only 2 indices but the device actually returns 3. The third
+               one always matches the second in my test, so I added this to make snmp-exporter work."
+       ::= { upsHighPrecBatteryPackEntry 2 }
+
    upsHighPrecBatteryPackIndex OBJECT-TYPE
        SYNTAX     INTEGER
        ACCESS     read-only
